r_c_next_from_future, last_step_cache\n    )\n\n    print(\"\\n--- Sanity Check for Backward Pass (Last Timestep) ---\")\n    print(f\"Shape of delta_W: {delta_W.shape} (Expected: {(hidden_size*4, input_size)})\")\n    print(f\"Shape of delta_U: {delta_U.shape} (Expected: {(hidden_size*4, hidden_size)})\")\n    print(f\"Shape of error_h_prev: {error_h_prev.shape} (Expected: {(hidden_size,)})\")\n    print(f\"Shape of error_c_prev: {error_c_prev.shape} (Expected: {(hidden_size,)})\")\n    \n    # Check if the shapes match the weight matrices\n    assert delta_W.shape \u003d\u003d hi_lstm.cell.W.weight.shape\n    assert delta_U.shape \u003d\u003d hi_lstm.cell.U.weight.shape\n    \n    print(\"\\n✅ Backward pass logic implemented and shapes are correct.\")\n```\n\n### **Summary of Implementation**\n\nYou now have a complete `HarmonicIntegerLSTMCell` with both a `forward` and a `backward` method.\n\n*   The **`forward`** pass now returns a `cache` of all intermediate values needed for learning.\n*   The **`backward`** pass takes the error from the next step and the `cache` and correctly calculates the integer-based updates for the weights (`delta_W`, `delta_U`) and the error signals to be passed to the previous step (`error_h_prev`, `error_c_prev`).\n\nThis is the fundamental engine of learning for our symbolic AI. The next and final step to complete the learning algorithm is to wrap this cell\u0027s backward pass inside the main `HarmonicIntegerLSTM` model\u0027s `backward` method, which will handle the **Backpropagation Through Time** loop as outlined previously.",
